# Cursor Master Prompt

## Protein & Fitness Laddoo ‚Äì Static Animated Website

> **Purpose of this document**
> This is the **single source of truth** prompt to be pasted into **Cursor**.
> It is intentionally explicit to prevent over-engineering, wrong frameworks, backend hallucinations, or animation abuse.
> This document will be refined iteratively as the build progresses.

---

## 1. Role & Objective

You are an **expert frontend engineer and UI developer**.

Your task is to **build a fully static, highly visual, animated website** for a brand called **‚ÄúProtein & Fitness Laddoo‚Äù**, strictly following the requirements and constraints below.

The final site must feel:

* Premium
* Warm & appetizing
* Modern fitness-focused (not clinical)
* Fast, smooth, and conversion-oriented

---

## 2. Core Constraints (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

### Deployment

* Must be deployable on **GitHub Pages**
* Must be a **fully static website**
* Use **only**:

  * HTML
  * CSS
  * JavaScript (ES6 modules)

üö´ **Do NOT use**:

* React, Vue, Angular, Svelte, Next.js
* Node.js servers
* Firebase / Supabase / backend APIs
* Build steps, bundlers, or CLIs
* Databases or authentication systems

---

## 3. Mandatory Tech Stack

* **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (via CDN or compiled static CSS)
* **Animations:** GSAP (GreenSock Animation Platform)

  * Use GSAP **only** for:

    * Hero section animations
    * ‚ÄúBuild Your Laddoo‚Äù configurator feedback
    * Scroll-based section reveals
  * Avoid animating every UI element
* **Icons:** Lucide Icons or Phosphor Icons (SVG-based)
* **State Management:** Client-side JavaScript only

---

## 3.1 Image Sourcing & Usage (IMPORTANT)

**Image Source Rules**

* Use **free, online-available images only** with permissive licenses
* Preferred sources:

  * Unsplash
  * Pexels
  * Pixabay
* Do NOT hotlink images; download and store them locally in the repo
* Always choose images that match the brand style (warm, food-focused, premium)

**Image Style Reference**

* Follow the visual direction shown in the **sample website mockup image** previously shared:

  * Large hero laddoo close-ups
  * Floating ingredient elements around the product
  * Clean, modern layout with strong imagery
  * Soft shadows and warm lighting

**Placeholders**

* If exact images are not available, use high-quality placeholders from the sources above
* Image filenames should clearly indicate intent (e.g., hero-laddoo.jpg, badam-laddoo.jpg)

---

* **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (via CDN or compiled static CSS)
* **Animations:** GSAP (GreenSock Animation Platform)

  * Use GSAP **only** for:

    * Hero section animations
    * ‚ÄúBuild Your Laddoo‚Äù configurator feedback
    * Scroll-based section reveals
  * Avoid animating every UI element
